---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../components/HeroSection.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Natred's terms of service governing IT support, consulting, and technology services. South African jurisdiction."
>
  <HeroSection
    title="Terms of Service"
    subtitle="Governing our engagement"
    compact={true}
    showCta={false}
  />

  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="policy-content">
        <div class="policy-intro animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <p class="last-updated">Last updated: February 2026</p>
          <p class="intro-text">These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your engagement of Avian Forge (Pty) Ltd, trading as Natred ("we," "us," "Natred"), for IT support, consulting, and related services. By engaging our services, you agree to these Terms.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>1. Definitions</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>"Client," "you":</strong> The individual or entity engaging Natred for services.</li>
            <li><strong>"Services":</strong> IT support, consulting, development, and related services provided by Natred.</li>
            <li><strong>"Agreement":</strong> These Terms together with any proposal, quote, or statement of work accepted by the Client.</li>
            <li><strong>"Deliverables":</strong> Any tangible outputs produced as part of the Services (code, documentation, configurations, etc.).</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>2. Services</h2>
          <h3>2.1 Scope</h3>
          <p>The scope of Services will be defined in proposals, quotes, or statements of work provided to you. Work outside the agreed scope may require additional fees.</p>

          <h3>2.2 Service Standards</h3>
          <p>We will perform Services with reasonable skill and care, consistent with industry standards. We will assign appropriately qualified personnel to your work.</p>

          <h3>2.3 No Guarantee of Results</h3>
          <p>While we strive for excellence, we cannot guarantee specific outcomes, system uptime, or that Services will be error-free. IT systems involve inherent complexities and dependencies outside our control.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>3. Client Responsibilities</h2>
          <p>To enable us to deliver Services effectively, you agree to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide timely access to systems, information, and personnel as reasonably required.</li>
            <li>Ensure you have necessary rights and authorizations for systems we work on.</li>
            <li>Maintain appropriate backups of your data (unless backup services are specifically included).</li>
            <li>Provide accurate information about your systems and requirements.</li>
            <li>Make decisions and provide approvals in a timely manner.</li>
            <li>Comply with software licences and terms of third-party services.</li>
            <li>Notify us promptly of any issues or concerns.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>4. Fees and Payment</h2>
          <h3>4.1 Fees</h3>
          <p>Fees for Services will be as quoted or as set out in our rate card. We may adjust rates with 30 days' notice for ongoing engagements.</p>

          <h3>4.2 Invoicing</h3>
          <p>We invoice monthly for time-based work and on completion or milestones for project work, unless otherwise agreed. Invoices include itemised breakdowns of work performed.</p>

          <h3>4.3 Payment Terms</h3>
          <p>Payment is due within 14 days of invoice date unless otherwise agreed. Late payments may incur interest at 2% per month or the maximum rate permitted by law.</p>

          <h3>4.4 Expenses</h3>
          <p>Reasonable expenses incurred in performing Services (travel, software licences, hardware) will be recharged at cost plus handling, with prior approval for significant expenses.</p>

          <h3>4.5 Disputes</h3>
          <p>If you dispute any invoice, notify us within 7 days with specific details. Undisputed portions remain due according to normal terms.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>5. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <h3>5.1 Client Materials</h3>
          <p>You retain ownership of all materials you provide to us (data, logos, content, etc.).</p>

          <h3>5.2 Deliverables</h3>
          <p>Upon full payment, you own custom Deliverables created specifically for you. This excludes our pre-existing tools, templates, methodologies, and general know-how.</p>

          <h3>5.3 Pre-Existing IP</h3>
          <p>We retain ownership of our pre-existing intellectual property, tools, and methodologies. You receive a non-exclusive licence to use such materials as incorporated into Deliverables.</p>

          <h3>5.4 Open Source</h3>
          <p>Where Deliverables incorporate open-source components, those components remain subject to their respective licences.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>6. Confidentiality</h2>
          <p>Each party agrees to keep confidential the other's confidential information disclosed during the engagement. Confidential information excludes information that is:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Publicly available through no fault of the receiving party</li>
            <li>Already known to the receiving party</li>
            <li>Independently developed without use of confidential information</li>
            <li>Rightfully received from a third party</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Confidentiality obligations survive termination for 3 years.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>7. Data Protection</h2>
          <p>We handle personal information in accordance with our Privacy Policy and applicable data protection laws, including POPIA. Where we process personal information on your behalf, we do so as your operator/processor under your instructions.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <h3>8.1 Exclusions</h3>
          <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, we exclude liability for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Indirect, consequential, or incidental damages</li>
            <li>Loss of profits, revenue, data, or business opportunity</li>
            <li>Damages arising from third-party products or services</li>
            <li>Damages caused by your breach of these Terms or misuse of Services</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>8.2 Cap</h3>
          <p>Our total liability for any claim arising from Services is limited to the fees paid to us for the specific Services giving rise to the claim, or R50,000, whichever is greater.</p>

          <h3>8.3 Exceptions</h3>
          <p>Nothing in these Terms excludes liability for fraud, gross negligence, or any liability that cannot be excluded by law.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>9. Warranties and Disclaimers</h2>
          <p>We warrant that Services will be performed with reasonable skill and care. To the maximum extent permitted by law, all other warranties, express or implied, are excluded.</p>
          <p>We do not warrant that Services will be uninterrupted, error-free, or that all defects will be corrected.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>10. Termination</h2>
          <h3>10.1 By Either Party</h3>
          <p>Either party may terminate ongoing Services with 30 days' written notice.</p>

          <h3>10.2 For Cause</h3>
          <p>Either party may terminate immediately if the other materially breaches these Terms and fails to cure within 14 days of notice.</p>

          <h3>10.3 Effect of Termination</h3>
          <p>Upon termination:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>You pay for Services rendered up to termination</li>
            <li>We deliver any completed Deliverables upon payment</li>
            <li>Each party returns or destroys the other's confidential information</li>
            <li>Provisions intended to survive termination continue in effect</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>11. Dispute Resolution</h2>
          <h3>11.1 Negotiation</h3>
          <p>Parties will attempt to resolve disputes through good faith negotiation.</p>

          <h3>11.2 Mediation</h3>
          <p>If negotiation fails, parties agree to attempt mediation before litigation.</p>

          <h3>11.3 Jurisdiction</h3>
          <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the Republic of South Africa. The courts of South Africa have exclusive jurisdiction over disputes arising from these Terms.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>12. General</h2>
          <h3>12.1 Entire Agreement</h3>
          <p>These Terms, together with applicable proposals and statements of work, constitute the entire agreement between the parties.</p>

          <h3>12.2 Amendment</h3>
          <p>We may update these Terms from time to time. Material changes will be communicated with 30 days' notice. Continued use of Services constitutes acceptance of updated Terms.</p>

          <h3>12.3 Assignment</h3>
          <p>Neither party may assign rights under these Terms without written consent, except in connection with a merger or acquisition.</p>

          <h3>12.4 Force Majeure</h3>
          <p>Neither party is liable for delays or failures caused by events beyond reasonable control.</p>

          <h3>12.5 Severability</h3>
          <p>If any provision is found unenforceable, the remaining provisions continue in effect.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-section animate-on-scroll fade-up">
          <h2>13. Contact</h2>
          <p>For questions about these Terms:</p>
          <div class="contact-info">
            <p><strong>Avian Forge (Pty) Ltd (trading as Natred)</strong></p>
            <p>Registration: 2024/212590/07</p>
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:service@natred.com">service@natred.com</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .policy-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .policy-intro {
    margin-bottom: 50px;
    padding-bottom: 30px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--dark-gray);
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--natred-orange);
    font-size: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .intro-text {
    color: var(--light-gray);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .policy-section {
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    padding-bottom: 40px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--dark-gray);
  }

  .policy-section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .policy-section h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .policy-section h3 {
    font-size: 18px;
    margin-top: 25px;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .policy-section p {
    color: var(--light-gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
  }

  .policy-section ul {
    margin-top: 15px;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    padding-left: 0;
  }

  .policy-section li {
    color: var(--light-gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    padding-left: 25px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .policy-section li::before {
    content: '\2022';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--natred-orange);
  }

  .policy-section li strong {
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .contact-info {
    background: var(--charcoal);
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--natred-orange);
    margin-top: 15px;
  }

  .contact-info p {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .contact-info p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .contact-info a {
    color: var(--natred-orange);
    transition: color var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .contact-info a:hover {
    color: var(--white);
  }
</style>
